result.execSummary:
Coby Dennis Moore was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Coby Dennis Moore was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Coby Dennis Moore not in court, defendant in custody.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case was scheduled on the 6-17-2015 calendar, however, Branch 20 was in trial, so case was called on today's date.    Defendant has been turned over to the State of Georgia.  Court orders case closed.
Branch 20 not in session on 6/09/15.  Case is rescheduled to 6/17/15 at 8:30 a.m.  File retained in court.

Defendant Coby Dennis Moore in court with attorney Nathan Opland-Dobs.  Defendant Coby Dennis Moore in custody.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The Court is in receipt of the Governor's Warrant from Jonesboro, Georgia and finds that the extradition warrant is appropriate.  Defendant is served with the extradition warrant in court.  Court ordered the defendant remanded into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department and awaiting pick up by the State of Georgia.  The Court orders case adjourned to make sure that the requesting state has picked up the defendant.  Court ordered case adjourned for status before Branch 20 on 6/09/15 at 8:30 a.m.  File retained in court.
Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.
Bail motion by defense argued and denied by the Court.  Same bail.

Defendant Coby Dennis Moore in court with attorney Nathan Opland-Dobs.  Defendant Coby Dennis Moore in custody.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Governor's warrant was not received.  Court ordered case continued before Branch 20.  Extradition hearing scheduled for May 26, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Nathan Opland-Dobs in court.  Deann L Heard appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Still waiting on Governor's warrant.  Defendant has been in custody over 30 days.  Defense requests court discharge defendant.  Court denies request.  May 26, 2015 is the last day for extradition to proceed.  Further proceedings scheduled for April 30, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Coby Dennis Moore in court with attorney Victoria Mccandless.  Defendant Coby Dennis Moore in custody.  Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  bm   Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Moroney, Branch 20.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of Georgia.  Defendant contested extradition.  Court ordered Defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Status conference scheduled for March 27, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
